{'type': {'name': 'type/page'}, 'name': 'dev/docs/setup', 'd': {'body': 'Requires:\r\n\r\n* Mercural (`hg`)\r\n* PostgreSQL (`psql`)\r\n* Python 2.5 or later (`python`)\r\n* [Psycopg2][] - Python driver for PostgreSQL\r\n\r\n[Psycopg2]: http://www.initd.org/tracker/psycopg/wiki/PsycopgTwo\r\n\r\n_Note:_ "Pharos", the name of the lighthouse of Alexandria, is the internal name for the Open Library.\r\n\r\nSetup:\r\n\r\n    $ hg clone http://demo.openlibrary.org:9021 pharos\r\n    $ cd pharos\r\n    $ ./setup.sh\r\n    $ cd pharos\r\n    $ createdb pharos\r\n    $ psql pharos < infogami/tdb/schema.sql\r\n    $ cp sample_run.py run.py\r\n    $# Edit run.py to change database settings\r\n    $ python run.py install\r\n    $ python run.py load dump.txt\r\n\r\nRun:\r\n\r\n    $ python run.py\r\n', 'title': 'How to install your own copy of the Open Library'}}